The '''Puducherry Prevention of Anti-Social Activities Act, 2008''' (PPASA) is an act of the [[Puducherry Legislative Assembly|Puducherry assembly]] which provides for preventive detention of boot-leggers, dangerous persons, forest offenders, gamblers, ''[[goonda]]s'' and property grabbers for prevention of their anti-social and dangerous activities prejudicial to the maintenance of public order.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://police.pondicherry.gov.in/THE%20PUDUCHERRY%20PREVENTION%20OF%20ANTI-SOCIAL%20ACTIVITIES%20ACT.pdf |format=PDF |title=The Gazette of Puducherry : THE PUDUCHERRY PREVENTION OF ANTI-SOCIAL ACTIVITIES ACT, 2008 |date=17 December 2010 |website=Police.pondicherry.gov |accessdate=2016-12-29}}</ref>

The bill was introduced in the assembly on 20 October 2008,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oneindia.com/2008/10/20/bill-to-curb-anti-social-activities-introduced-1224502989.html|title=Bill to curb anti-social activities introduced|date=20 October 2008|website=Oneindia.com |accessdate=2016-12-29}}</ref> and the act came into effect from 27 October 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/modified-prevention-of-antisocial-activities-bill-passed/article856740.ece |title=Modified Prevention of Anti-social Activities Bill passed - TAMIL NADU |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |date=2010-10-29 |accessdate=2016-09-18}}</ref>

